<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="21">
Fishes of the eelpout genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:555B344D-5775-4AF5-A583-0AE42162235B" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Pachycara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachycara Zugmayer 1911:12" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachycara</taxonomicName>
inhabit the upper slopes and abyssal plains of most regions, but are notably absent in the western Pacific, Mediterranean Sea and Arctic Ocean (Anderson 1989). Seven species have been described since the senior author’s 1989 paper (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Møller">Moller</normalizedToken>
2003; Anderson and Fedorov, 2004; Biscoito and Almeida, 2004). Less than half (38%) of the species occur in the bathyal zone; the rest are abyssal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
